  "prompt": "What is difference between living for work and work for living?",
  "response": "The difference between \"living for work\" and \"working for living\" revolves around the central focus of an individual's life and their motivations:\n\n1. **Living for Work**:\n   - People who live for work prioritize their careers above most other aspects of life.\n   - Their job is a principal source of identity, satisfaction, purpose, and happiness.\n   - They often invest a significant amount of time, energy, and passion into their work.\n   - This can sometimes lead to neglecting personal relationships, hobbies, health, and leisure activities due to the dominance of work in their lives.\n\n2. **Working for Living**:\n   - People who work for living view their job primarily as a means to earn money and support their lifestyle.\n   - Their work is not the most important aspect of their lives; it serves the function of providing financial stability.\n   - They usually maintain a clearer separation between work and personal life, allocating time for family, hobbies, rest, and other interests.\n   - They may seek fulfillment outside their work, whereas work might not be their primary source of identity or satisfaction.\n\nBoth approaches have their own implications for personal fulfillment, work-life balance, and overall well-being. It is important for individuals to find a balance that works for their unique circumstances and personal values.",
